<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>258</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001E</addr>  <route>axt-001E.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author> </authors> <title>Small basis (of algebraicity) for a dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  For a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex>, a <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> on <tex>D</tex> with
  <tex>B :  \mathcal{V}</tex> is a <em>small basis</em> for <tex>D</tex> if the following conditions hold:
  <ol>    <li>      for every <tex>x : D</tex>, the <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family">family</link> <tex>(( \sum _{b : B}  \beta (b)  \ll       x),  \beta   \circ   \mathsf{pr} _1 )</tex> is directed and has supremum <tex>x</tex>;
    </li>    <li>      for every <tex>x : D</tex> and <tex>b : B</tex>, the proposition <tex>\beta (b)  \ll  x</tex> is
      <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-small.
    </li>  </ol></p><p>  Adapted from <b>Definition 4.6.7</b> of <link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local" title="Tom de Jong">Tom de Jong</link>'s <link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">PhD thesis</link>.
</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>259</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001F</addr>  <route>axt-001F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author>Ayberk Tosun</author> </authors> <title>ùì•-Family</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <em><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family on a type <tex>A :  \mathcal{U}</tex></em> is a pair <tex>(I,  \iota )</tex> where
  <ul>    <li><tex>I</tex> is a type in universe <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>,</li>    <li>and <tex>\iota</tex> is a function of type <tex>I  \to  A</tex>.</li>  </ul></p><p>  List of formal definitions:
  <ol>    <li>      <link href="https://www.cs.bham.ac.uk//~mhe/TypeTopology/Slice.Family.html#262" type="external">Fam in UF.Slice</link>      in TypeTopology.
